  "prompt": "What is the biggest turn off for girls in opposite sex?",
  "response": "While individual preferences can vary widely, there are several common turn-offs for many women when it comes to the opposite sex. Some of the biggest ones include:\n\n1. **Lack of Respect:** Disrespectful behavior towards others or towards the woman herself, including sexist or derogatory remarks.\n\n2. **Poor Hygiene:** Neglecting personal cleanliness can be a significant turn-off.\n\n3. **Dishonesty:** Being dishonest or deceitful can severely undermine trust and is often viewed very negatively.\n\n4. **Arrogance:** Overconfidence or a condescending attitude can be very unattractive.\n\n5. **Lack of Ambition:** Not having goals or motivation in life can be unappealing to some women who value ambition.\n\n6. **Inability to Communicate:** Poor communication skills or an unwillingness to engage in meaningful conversations.\n\n7. **Insecurity:** Excessive jealousy or neediness can be off-putting.\n\n8. **Emotional Unavailability:** Being closed off emotionally and unable to share feelings or connect deeply.\n\n9. **Lack of Humor:** A poor sense of humor or inability to enjoy fun moments can be a drawback.\n\n10. **Selfishness:** Being inconsiderate or self-centered can be a significant negative trait. \n\nIt's important to remember that everyone has their own unique preferences, and what one person may find unattractive, another might not mind or even appreciate. Communication and understanding individual values are key in any relationship.",
